<br>
First charge was called at 10:18<br>
<br>
At 10:20 I was slain by Lord Nagafen, his health at the time was at 'Lord'<br>
<br>
At 10:30, Dehna from my group informed me that Naggy had been slain =)<br>
<br>
10:33 I was rezed back in, Ballaanea had been doing her best to lock the corpse since her group had gotten the XP, but by that time the Cloak of Flames had been Plooted.<br>
<br>
(While holding a corpse, after some amount of time you are popped off of the corpse and you have to reloot. The cloak of flames was the first thing Ballaanea informed me that had dropped and when she got back on the corpse after being popped off of it, it was gone.)<br>
<br>
Anyways, after some work Xetulous recovered the CoF from the plooter, who presumably had logged.. apparently in Rivervale. I know many would like to know who did this, but Xetulous wouldn't divulge this information.<br>
<br>
In the end the Cloak of Flames was recovered and that's what matters, the roll was won by Fragoth, big congrats to him!<br>
<br>
Other drops and who won them are:<br>
<br>
Gauntlets of Fiery Might: I rolled all melee, it went to Dehna<br>
<br>
Gold Plated Koshigatan: Thundore (who was assigned 2, which he had been complaining was a number that never got rolled. hehe)<br>
<br>
Treasure Hunter's Satchel: Elwolvie (whom I need to find, meanwhile you're on my friends list so I can find ya!)<br>
<br>
We had 7 full groups and I believe 2 more in group 8. Thanks again to everyone that came! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uballaaneapolarwytch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ballaanea Polarwytch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(7/21/01 9:30:12 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy, bind rushes, and plooters (who never win)</span><hr size=1> Ya live and ya learn.  I didn't know you could only loot a corpse for a limited amount of time.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     I am SO glad the cloak was recovered, I was heartsick about it, and it put a damper on what was a thrilling experience.  Shame on you, whoever you were!<br>
<br>
Congrats to Fragoth!  He kept our group wonderfully entertained during the downtimes.  What a wonderful bard!<br>
<br>
It was a great night for Diablerie, I got dragon xp for the first time (he redinged me to 51 after killing me 6 times <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ), and two of my guildies, Dehna and Elwolvie, got their first dragon loot!<br>
<br>
Thank you very much for the experience you have granted to our wee band of adventurers Xorshaik!  And more thanks to Ahjess, Alihja, Alissa, and Gyries for rezzing all my corpses! <p><BR>
<BR>
<BIG><FONT COLOR="##871f78">Ballaanea Polarwytch</BIG><BR>
Tribunal Mystic of 51 Winters<BR>
Grand Matriarch and Tour Guide of <a href=http://diablerie.zogdog.net>Diablerie</a></FONT></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uballaaneapolarwytch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ballaanea Polarwytch</A> at: 7/21/01 10:44:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uraleldorjax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raleldor Jax</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(7/21/01 10:11:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Naggy, bind rushes, and plooters (who never win)</span><hr size=1> I was in the zone while you guys were trying to kill him.. it seems you had lost it but i guess the rezzes came fast enough to take him away from that last sliver of life. <p><a href="http://www.xmission.com/~garetjax/index2.html"><img src="http://www.xmission.com/~garetjax/images/EQpics/Rall.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uxorshaik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xorshaik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(7/21/01 12:23:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hehe..</span><hr size=1> I'm sure it was very much from the casters (who bind near the lair) charging back in and stubbornly refusing to let him regenerate his life and keeping at it until they managed to get off enough nukes.. From what I heard, he kept summoning and it made things hard to get a nuke off.<br>
<br>
On one hand I'll be working a little bit to try to make sure I improve some instructions or maybe hold the melee not on the first charge a little later so they can give the casters more time to nuke..<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I think it's not bad for having had to gather folks mostly based on e-mails and posts that all went out the same day, and having about 42 people there, of which around 75% haven't been on one of my dragon raids before. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I can't really say I've had a dragon raid yet where I've truly felt everything went right, but when it comes to the bottom line.. The dragon died, and everyone's pretty happy. That's nothing to complain about =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/usyrana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syrana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(7/21/01 12:45:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hehe..</span><hr size=1> Xorshaik, I had a blast!  Thank you again for putting on these raids.  It let's those of us that are not in an uber guild to have some of the fun too.  I can't tell you how much it is appreciated.<br>
<br>
And even if you feel they don't go right, you're doing a very good job.  The people I've talked with have been happy with your leadership, planning, and abilities.  In the end, the dragon dies, and that is what matters. <p>--------------------------------------------------<BR>
Syrana, 42nd Ranger, always looking for trouble<BR>
Dyrna, 45th Druid, always trying to get out of trouble<BR>
